%20up%20to%20pink%20and%20purple%20to%20the%20north%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655bcd9f4ca513d8242c88e6%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%202023%20USDA%20%26quot%3Bplant%20hardiness%26quot%3B%20map%20shows%20some%20changed%20growing%20zones%20since%20the%202012%20version.%3Cp%3EUS%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20USDA%20updated%20its%20map%20of%20plant%20hardiness%20zones%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20over%20a%20decade.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20new%20map%20shows%20that%20half%20the%20country%20has%20shifted%20to%20warmer%20zones.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20updated%20zones%20could%20allow%20gardeners%20to%20grow%20plants%20that%20they%20never%20could%20before.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20USDA%20has%20updated%20its%20plant%20hardiness%20zone%20map%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%20over%2010%20years.%20The%20new%20map%20could%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fgardening-qurantine-financial-independence-more-than-money-2020-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Echange%20how%20you%20garden%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGardening%20consultant%2C%20Megan%20London%2C%20for%20example%2C%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2023%2F11%2F17%2F1213600629%2F-it-feels-like-im-not-crazy-gardeners-arent-surprised-as-usda-updates-key-map%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENPR%3C%2Fa%3E%20she's%20now%20considering%20growing%20an%20array%20of%20new%20treats%20including%20kumquats%20and%20mandarin%20oranges%20in%20her%20gardens%20in%20central%20Arkansas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20new%20map%2C%20central%20Arkansas%20shifted%20half%20a%20zone%20up%20from%20zone%207b%20to%20zone%208a%20since%20the%20USDA%20last%20updated%20its%20map%20in%202012.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20are%20plant%20zones%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20USDA's%20map%20is%20the%20national%20standard%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fgardening-tools-for-beginners%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elets%20gardeners%20and%20growers%20know%3C%2Fa%3E%20what%20types%20of%20perennial%20plants%20%E2%80%94%20plants%20that%20return%20year%20after%20year%20%E2%80%94%20are%20most%20likely%20to%20thrive%20in%20certain%20locations.%20The%20map%20categorizes%20these%20locations%20by%20zones%20and%20half%20zones%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplanthardiness.ars.usda.gov%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20USDA%20said%20on%20its%20website%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20is%20divided%20into%2013%20growing%20zones.%20Each%20zone%20represents%20the%20average%20lowest%20winter%20temperature%20an%20area%20typically%20sees%20every%20year%2C%20per%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fplanthardiness.ars.usda.gov%2Fpages%2Fhow-to-use-the-maps%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUSDA%3C%2Fa%3E.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20good%20chunk%20of%20southern%20Florida%2C%20for%20example%2C%20is%20zone%2010b%20(35%20to%2040%20degrees%20Fahrenheit)%20while%20northern%20Montana%20has%20pockets%20of%20zone%203b%20(-35%20to%20-30%20degrees%20Fahrenheit).%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20plants%20native%20to%20the%20US%20are%20equipped%20to%20survive%20in%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20zones%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhg.com%2Fgardening%2Fgardening-by-region%2Fhow-to-use-hardiness-zone-information%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBetter%20Homes%20%26amp%3B%20Gardens%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Some%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bhg.com%2Fgardening%2Fflowers%2Fperennials%2Ftough-perennials-that-grow-in-dry-shade%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eferns%20and%20grasses%3C%2Fa%3E%20can%20thrive%20in%20zones%204%20through%209%2C%20for%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThis%20is%20all%20about%20winter%20cold%2C%20this%20map%2C%26quot%3B%20Chris%20Daly%2C%20director%20of%20the%20PRISM%20Climate%20Group%20at%20Oregon%20State%20University%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIt%20has%20nothing%20to%20do%20with%20planting%20zones%20in%20terms%20of%20when%20you%20plant%20or%20what%20can%20survive%20the%20summer.%26quot%3B%20He%20helped%20develop%20the%20map%20along%20with%20the%20USDA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EHalf%20of%20the%20US%20has%20shifted%20to%20warmer%20plant%20zones%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20maps%20on%20top%20of%20each%20other%20showing%20the%202023%20(above)%20and%202012%20USDA%20'plant%20hardiness'%20zones%20in%20the%20Southeastern%20US%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655bd74922cf74a5739a7e1c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ECentral%20and%20northern%20Florida%20and%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20Southeastern%20US%20have%20changed%20zones%20on%20the%202023%20map%20(top).%3Cp%3EUS%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20map%20for%202023%20has%20pushed%20half%20the%20country%20into%20a%20warmer%20half%20zone%2C%20while%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20country%20has%20remained%20in%20the%20same%20zone%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ars.usda.gov%2Fnews-events%2Fnews%2Fresearch-news%2F2023%2Fusda-unveils-updated-plant-hardiness-zone-map%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20USDA%20said%20in%20a%20press%20release%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20maps%20on%20top%20of%20each%20other%20showing%20the%202023%20(above)%20and%202012%20USDA%20'plant%20hardiness'%20zones%20in%20the%20Northeastern%20US%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655bd0b64ca513d8242c8c12%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%202023%20USDA%20map%20shows%20warmer%20zones%20in%20central%20Michigan%2C%20as%20well%20as%20shifts%20in%20some%20Northeastern%20states.%3Cp%3EUS%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20some%20areas%20of%20Omaha%2C%20Nebraska%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Flancaster.unl.edu%2Fhort%2Fmastergardener%2Fresources%2FNE%2520USDA%2520Plan%2520Hardiness%2520Zone%2520Map.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Ehave%20moved%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%205b%20to%206a.%20Meaning%20that%20the%20average%20lowest%20winter%20temperature%20for%20that%20region%20rose%20from%20between%20-15%20and%20-10%20degrees%20Fahrenheit%20to%20-10%20to%20-5%20degrees%20Fahrenheit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20maps%2C%20side-by-side%2C%20showing%20the%20USDA%20Plant%20Hardiness%20Zones%20in%20North%20Central%20US%20in%202023%20and%202012%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655bcf659c7d23cb3b9db793%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20the%20North%20Central%20US%2C%20some%20of%20the%20coldest%20zones%20have%20disappeared%20from%20northern%20Minnesota%20in%202023%20(left)%20compared%20to%202012%20(right).%3Cp%3EUS%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20changes%20could%20mean%20a%20shift%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbuilt-side-business-plant-kween-social-media-heres-how-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewhat%20will%20grow%20best%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20your%20garden.%20When%20you're%20purchasing%20perennials%2C%20you'll%20often%20see%20their%20zone%20ranges%20listed%2C%20Daly%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20growers%20should%20be%20cautious%2C%20Jonathan%20Foster%2C%20a%20horticulture%20outreach%20professional%2C%20wrote%20on%20The%20University%20of%20Maine's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fextension.umaine.edu%2Fgardening%2Fmanual%2Fusda-plant-hardiness-zone-map%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMaine%20Gardner%20Manual%3C%2Fa%3E%20site.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ELimitations%20of%20the%20USDA's%20new%20plant%20zone%20map%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20map%20is%20a%20guideline%2C%20not%20a%20guarantee%2C%26quot%3B%20Foster%20wrote%2C%20and%20plants%20can%20thrive%20in%20several%20zones.%20However%2C%20you'll%20want%20to%20consider%20other%20factors%2C%20like%20summer%20temperatures%20and%20soil%20quality%20as%20well.%20The%20map%20doesn't%20reflect%20these%20nuances.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20maps%20on%20top%20of%20each%20other%20showing%20the%202023%20(above)%20and%202012%20USDA%20'plant%20hardiness'%20zones%20in%20the%20Southwestern%20US%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655bd6b422cf74a5739a7dbf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20zone%20shifts%20in%20the%20Southwestern%20US%20for%20the%202023%20map%20(top)%20aren't%20as%20widespread%20as%20other%20areas%20of%20the%20country.%3Cp%3EUS%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EFoster%20also%20noted%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fhouseplant-care-products%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emore%20delicate%20plants%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20like%20poppies%2C%20might%20not%20fare%20as%20well%20as%20hardier%20trees%20and%20shrubs%20in%20snowy%20climates%20like%20Maine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20map%20is%20also%20limited%20in%20how%20detailed%20it%20can%20get%2C%20Daly%20said.%20Your%20garden%20might%20get%20more%20sun%20than%20your%20neighbors%20or%20have%20shadier%20spots%20thanks%20to%20trees.%20%26quot%3BThose%20may%20have%20microclimates%20that%20are%20warmer%20or%20colder%20than%20what%20the%20zone%20says%20that%20you%20are%2C%26quot%3B%20Daly%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20caused%20half%20the%20US%20to%20shift%20to%20a%20warmer%20zone%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20USDA%20said%20that%20the%20shift%20to%20warmer%20zones%20is%20%26quot%3Bnot%20necessarily%20reflective%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclimate-crisis-comedians-jokes-drive-change-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eglobal%20climate%20change%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20because%20several%20factors%20contributed%20to%20the%20changes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Side-by-side%20maps%20showing%20the%202023%20(left)%20and%202012%20USDA%20'plant%20hardiness'%20zones%20in%20the%20Northwestern%20US%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655bd1cf4ca513d8242c8d91%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIn%20the%20Northwestern%20US%2C%20the%202023%20USDA%20map%20(left)%20shows%20some%20regions%20of%20Montana%20in%20new%2C%20warmer%20zones.%3Cp%3EUS%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EDaly%20and%20the%20USDA%20used%20data%20from%201991%20to%202020%20and%20chose%20the%20coldest%20night%20of%20the%20year.%20%26quot%3BWe%20only%20have%2030%20numbers%20that%20we're%20averaging%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20Daly%20said.%20That's%20why%20it's%20important%20to%20look%20at%20decades%20of%20data%2C%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20temperature%20on%20the%20coldest%20night%20can%20shift%20for%20a%20variety%20of%20reasons%20aside%20from%20climate%20change.%20One%20year%20might%20not%20have%20a%20cold%20snap%2C%20and%20the%20next%20winter's%20could%20be%20particularly%20harsh%2C%20Daly%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20map%20is%20also%20based%20on%20information%20from%20thousands%20more%20weather%20stations%2C%20according%20to%20the%20USDA.%20It%20pulled%20data%20from%2013%2C412%20weather%20stations%20compared%20to%207%2C983%20for%20the%202012%20map%2C%20per%20the%20USDA's%20press%20release.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDaly%20developed%20Prism%2C%20the%20software%20that%20created%20the%20map.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20really%20good%20at%20reproducing%20the%20effects%20of%20features%20on%20the%20Earth's%20surface%2C%20such%20as%20mountains%2C%20valleys%2C%20and%20coastlines%2C%20on%20climatic%20patterns%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20It%20helped%20make%20the%20map%20more%20detailed%20and%20accurate%20than%20previous%20versions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20interactive.%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20enter%20your%20zip%20code%20or%20you%20can%20click%20anywhere%20in%20the%20map%20and%20zoom%20and%20pan%20on%20it%20and%20see%20what%20your%20zone%20is%2C%26quot%3B%20Daly%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20climate%20change%20is%20influencing%20plant%20hardiness%20zones%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20grand%20scheme%20of%20things%2C%20climate%20change%20is%20influencing%20where%20plants%20can%20grow%2C%20Daly%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Side-by-side%20maps%20showing%20the%202023%20(above)%20and%202012%20USDA%20'plant%20hardiness'%20zones%20in%20the%20South%20Central%20US%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655bd2904ca513d8242c8efa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESections%20of%20the%20South%20Central%20US%2C%20including%20Houston%2C%20Texas%2C%20and%20New%20Orleans%2C%20Louisiana%2C%20have%20changed%20to%20new%20zones%20in%20the%202023%20USDA%20map%20(left).%3Cp%3EUS%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20know%20for%20a%20fact%20that%20average%20temperatures%20are%20rising%20due%20to%20climate%20change.%20There's%20no%20doubt%20about%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20Daly%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20I%20think%20over%20the%20long%20term%2C%20this%20should%20cause%20plant%20hardiness%20zones%20to%20gradually%20shift%20northward.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fusda-unveils-first-new-plant-zone-hardiness-map-over-decade-2023-11%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700531142000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655bcdc49c7d23cb3b9db614%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fusda-unveils-first-new-plant-zone-hardiness-map-over-decade-2023-11%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22USDA%20unveils%20its%20new%20plant%20zone%20hardiness%20map.%20Half%20of%20the%20country%20has%20moved%20up%20to%20a%20warmer%20half%20zone%2C%20the%20United%20States%20Department%20of%20Agriculture%20said.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22ggoodwin%40businessinsider.com%20(Grace%20Eliza%20Goodwin%2CJenny%20McGrath)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fusda-unveils-first-new-plant-zone-hardiness-map-over-decade-2023-11%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Explains%20the%20Political%20Right%E2%80%99s%20Ascendancy%20to%20Global%20Power%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F09%2F12140727%2FIMG_3148.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20is%20the%20second%20part%20of%20a%20two-part%20review%20analysis%20based%20on%20the%20key%20findings%20in%20Oleksandr%20Svitych%E2%80%99s%20recent%20book%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbrill.com%2Fdisplay%2Ftitle%2F62356%3Flanguage%3Den%5C%22%3EThe%20Rise%20of%20the%20Capital-State%20and%20Neo-Nationalism%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%2C%20which%20attempts%20to%20provide%20a%20political%20economy%20approach%20to%20the%20rise%20of%20%E2%80%98neo-nationalism%E2%80%99%20%E2%80%93%20a%20populist%20form%20of%20nationalism%20observed%20in%20the%20contemporary%20globalised%20period.%20Read%20the%20first%20part%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fhow-neo-nationalism-has-fuelled-the-transformation-of-old-welfare-state-to-new-capital-state%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20our%20own%20book%20%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.routledge.com%2FStrongmen-Saviours-A-Political-Economy-of-Populism-in-India-Turkey-Russia%2FMohan-Padmanabhan%2Fp%2Fbook%2F9781032288314%5C%22%3EStrongmen%20Saviours%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20our%20comparative%20political%20economy%20analysis%20in%20explaining%20the%20recent%20wave%20of%20right-wing%20populist%20movements%20across%20the%20world%20was%20explained%20through%20a%20distinct%20pattern%20exhibiting%20features%20that%20have%20been%20unique%20to%20the%20nature%20of%20right-wing%20movements%20(as%20against%20left-wing%20movements%20of%20the%20past).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20purpose%20then%20was%20to%20provide%20a%20comparative%20socio-political%2C%20economic%20explanation%20of%20the%20rise%20of%20populist%20beliefs%20and%20anti-political%20elite%20sentiment%20that%20has%20not%20captured%20much%20of%20the%20Western%20and%20non-Western%20sphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20pyramid%20constructed%20below%2C%20drawn%20from%20our%20book%E2%80%99s%20research%2C%20may%20offer%20some%20insights%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20984px)%2061vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2045vw%2C%20600px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F20181018%2FDM1.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F20181018%2FDM1.png%20720w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F20181018%2FDM1-300x189.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685559%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22454%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESource%3A%20Author%E2%80%99s%20graphic%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20conceptual%20pyramid%20attempts%20to%20unpack%20features%20of%20right-wing%20populism%2C%20operating%20under%20the%20guise%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.routledge.com%2FStrongmen-Saviours-A-Political-Economy-of-Populism-in-India-Turkey-Russia%2FMohan-Padmanabhan%2Fp%2Fbook%2F9781032288314%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98ideological%20populism%E2%80%99%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0(ideologically%20aligned%20populist%20movements)%2C%20which%20has%20a%20distinct%20meaning%20(see%20a%20more%20detailed%20explainer%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Flive%2FPgPnQ3RmdqA%3Ffeature%3Dshare%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20simple%20terms%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-political-ethics-of-the-indian-political-right%5C%22%3Eideological%20populism%C2%A0%3C%2Fa%3Erefers%20to%20the%20unchecked%20and%20unabated%20rise%20of%20an%20ideology%2C%20the%20marginalisation%20of%20its%20moderate%20factions%2C%20involving%20the%20development%20of%20a%20cult-personality%20that%20infuses%20shades%20of%20populism%20into%20it.%20Normatively%2C%20this%20can%20be%20ideologically%20aligned%20towards%20the%20%E2%80%98political%20left%E2%80%99%20or%20the%20%E2%80%98political%20right%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20distinct%20characteristics%20of%20%3Cem%3Erightwing%20%3C%2Fem%3Epopulism%20at%20least%20the%20way%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.routledge.com%2FStrongmen-Saviours-A-Political-Economy-of-Populism-in-India-Turkey-Russia%2FMohan-Padmanabhan%2Fp%2Fbook%2F9781032288314%5C%22%3Ewe%20have%20observed%20in%20countries%20such%20as%20India%2C%20Turkey%2C%20Russia%20and%20Brazil%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0did%20see%20certain%20common%20features%2C%20across%20different%20times%20and%20spaces.%20I%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-political-ethics-of-the-indian-political-right%5C%22%3Eexplained%20a%20few%20of%20these%20factors%2Ffeatures%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20pyramid%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fopinion%2Fright-wing-populism-towards-a-new-theory-of-economic-change%23read-more%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20three%20contributing%20drivers%20for%20the%20Right%E2%80%99s%20authoritative%20rise%20to%20majoritarian%20power%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E1.%20Failure%20of%20neoliberalism%20(supply-side%20economics%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9990s)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20origins%20of%20each%20of%20these%20movements%20are%20sourced%20in%20the%20economic%20discontents%20of%20%E2%80%98neoliberalism%E2%80%99%20or%20the%20nature%20of%20supply-side%20economics%20(externally%20influenced%20by%20the%20West%2FWashington%20Consensus%20style%20reform%20packages)%20pursued%20in%20the%201990s.%20Studies%20from%20scholars%20like%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.annualreviews.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1146%2Fannurev-economics-070220-032416%5C%22%3ESides%20et%20al.%20(2018)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.annualreviews.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1146%2Fannurev-economics-070220-032416%5C%22%3ENorris%20%26amp%3B%20Inglehart%20(2019)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.annualreviews.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1146%2Fannurev-economics-070220-032416%5C%22%3EMargalit%20(2019)%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0also%20explain%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20wave%20of%20rise%20in%20religious%20conservatism%20or%20religious%20orthodoxy%20(from%20Hindutva%20to%20Orthodox%20Islam%20to%20Evangelical%20Catholicism)%20that%20aided%20the%20rise%20of%20each%20of%20the%20leaders%20who%20either%20belonged%20to%20political%20parties%20or%20to%20orthodox-religious%20based%20organisations%20which%20ensured%20an%20undercurrent%20of%20religious%20conservatism.%20I%20explain%20more%20about%20this%20phenomenon%20(as%20seen%20in%20India%2C%20Turkey%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20Brazil)%20in%20a%20lecture%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Flive%2FPgPnQ3RmdqA%3Ffeature%3Dshare%5C%22%3Egiven%20here.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20trigger%20factor%20which%20led%20to%20the%20mass-protest%20vote%20in%20favour%20of%20each%20strongman%20figure%20(from%20Modi%20to%20Bolsonaro)%2C%20was%20often%20related%20to%20either%20a%20series%20of%20big%20public%20corruption%20episodes%20or%20reported%20scandal(s)%20in%20the%20home%20country%E2%80%99s%20domestic%20political%20environment%2C%20which%20gave%20the%20opportunity%20for%20the%20mass-support%20in%20favour%20of%20an%20alternative%20imagination%20of%20%E2%80%98power%E2%80%99%20and%20a%20leader%2C%20someone%20outside%20the%20status%20quo%20ruling%20political%20elite-to%20come%20to%20power%2C%20and%20enjoy%20mass%20popularity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20India%20to%20Brazil%2C%20each%20of%20the%20countries%20we%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.routledge.com%2FStrongmen-Saviours-A-Political-Economy-of-Populism-in-India-Turkey-Russia%2FMohan-Padmanabhan%2Fp%2Fbook%2F9781032288314%5C%22%3Ediscuss%20in%20the%20book%3C%2Fa%3E%20saw%20episodes%20of%20public%20corruption%20(via%20scandals)%20or%20were%20operating%20in%20a%20widely%20%E2%80%98perceived%20environment%20of%20corruption%E2%80%99%20that%20made%20more%20of%20the%20popular%20vote%20pivot%20towards%20the%20choice%20of%20voting%20for%20an%20%E2%80%98alternative%E2%80%99%20(as%20also%20seen%20with%20the%20protest%20vote%20for%20Donald%20Trump%20in%20the%202016%20US%20presidential%20election).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20weaponisation%20of%20social%20media%20in%20a%20new%20tech-enabled%20information%20order%20made%20it%20possible%20for%20right-wing%20populists%20to%20continue%20feeding%20an%20alternative%2C%20post-truth%20rhetorical%20narrative%20(us%20vs%20them%20the%20axis%20of%20immigration)%20which%20not%20only%20helped%20them%20and%20their%20parties%20to%20constantly%20gain%20the%20support%20of%20a%20polarised%20%E2%80%98majority%E2%80%99%20(their%20own%20voter%20base)%2C%20but%20also%20help%20them%20sustain%2Fconsolidate%20and%20then%20later%20centralise%20power%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20others%20(those%20in%20minorities).%20Surveillance%20capitalism%20made%20this%20possible%20too%20under%20a%20new%20nexus%20of%20private%20capital-state%20relationship%20which%20supported%20%E2%80%98strongmen%E2%80%99%20figures%20in%20power%20through%20social%20media%20and%20digitised%20surveillance%20tools.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E2.%20Focus%20on%20privatisation%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20nature%20of%20fiscal%20policy%20and%20the%20fiscal%20choice%20made%20by%20each%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.routledge.com%2FStrongmen-Saviours-A-Political-Economy-of-Populism-in-India-Turkey-Russia%2FMohan-Padmanabhan%2Fp%2Fbook%2F9781032288314%5C%22%3Estrongmen%20figures%20(right-wing%20populists)%20in%20recent%20years%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0has%20been%20drastically%20varied%20when%20compared%20to%20the%20earlier%20regimes%20of%20populist%20movements%20(as%20seen%20say%20in%20Latin%20America)%20where%20strongmen%20leadership%20was%20influenced%20by%20a%20theory%20of%20economic%20and%20political%20change%20belonging%20to%20pro-welfare%2C%20left-leaning%20policies%20(which%20in%20some%20instances%20like%20Venezuela%20made%20governments%20fiscally%20indebted).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20variant%20of%20right-wing%20populism%20has%20seen%20a%20promotion%20of%20privatisation%20(a%20reorientation%20of%20previous%20state-private%20capital%20elite%20relationship)%20%E2%80%93%20pursued%20with%20gradual%20disinvestment%20of%20public%20assets%2C%20government%20ownership%20of%20resources%20(including%20a%20de-funding%20of%20social%20programmes%20targeted%20for%20areas%20of%20job%20creation%2C%20human%20capital%20development-healthcare%20and%20education).%20This%20is%20widely%20seen%20in%20the%20fiscal%20choices%20made%20by%20most%20strongmen%20figures%20(case%20in%20point%3A%20see%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20term%20of%20governance%20in%20India).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20this%2C%20they%20(strongmen)%20continue%20to%20strike%20a%20chord%20with%20extremely%20low-income%20voters%20in%20some%20of%20the%20lesser%20developed%20states%2Fprovinces%20by%20the%20deployed%20political%20use%20of%20specific%20targeted-beneficiary-based%20%E2%80%98welfare%20schemes%E2%80%99%20(say%2C%20free%20nutrition)%20to%20keep%20the%20more%20poor%20content%20and%20as%20part%20of%20a%20loyal%20voter%20base.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20must%20however%20be%20observed%20that%20none%20of%20this%20so-called%20%E2%80%98welfare%E2%80%99%20spending%20is%20aimed%20at%20the%20upward%20mobility%20of%20the%20low-income%20beneficiary%20(say%20through%20complementary%20support%20offered%20in%20human%20capital%20development%20%E2%80%93%20education%2C%20healthcare%20or%20job%20support%20plans).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E3.%20On%20contestations%20within%3A%20Hyper-globalism%20and%20ideological%20populism%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDani%20Rodrik%E2%80%99s%20recent%20work%20(%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.annualreviews.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1146%2Fannurev-economics-070220-032416%5C%22%3E2021%3C%2Fa%3E%3B%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrodrik.scholar.harvard.edu%2Fsites%2Fscholar.harvard.edu%2Ffiles%2Fdani-rodrik%2Ffiles%2Fon_productivism.pdf%5C%22%3E2023%3C%2Fa%3E)%20offers%20useful%20insights%20on%20at%20least%20addressing%20one%20of%20these%20%E2%80%98contested%E2%80%99%20conceptual%20questions%3A%20Why%20did%20globalisation%20of%20the%20post-1990s%20variant%20fuel%20a%20certain%20wave%20of%20populism%20(one%20that%20spread%20far%20across%20the%20west%20and%20the%20east)%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%E2%80%99s%20look%20at%20this%20one%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Rodrik%2C%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9CIt%20is%20important%20to%20understand%20what%20are%20the%20mechanisms%20through%20which%20globalization%20fuels%20populism.%20Answering%20this%20question%20requires%20a%20fully%20fleshed-out%20model%20of%20political%20economy.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESecond%2C%20globalization%20is%20not%20just%20one%20thing%3A%20We%20can%20distinguish%20between%20international%20trade%2C%20international%20finance%2C%20and%20international%20labor%20flows%2C%20specifically.%20How%20does%20each%20one%20of%20these%20facets%20of%20globalization%20work%20its%20way%20through%20the%20political%20system%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThird%2C%20globalization%20is%20clearly%20not%20the%20only%20economic%20shock%20that%20creates%20redistributive%20effects%20or%20economic%20anxiety%E2%80%94and%20it%20may%20not%20even%20be%20the%20most%20important%20one.%20Why%20does%20globalization%20appear%20to%20have%20an%20outsized%20effect%20on%20politics%20compared%20to%2C%20say%2C%20technological%20change%20or%20regular%20business%20cycles%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20aspects%20are%20studied%20more%20empirically%20by%20Rodrik%20in%20the%20framework%20created%20below%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20450px)%2085vw%2C%20450px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F20195700%2FDM2.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F20195700%2FDM2.png%20626w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F20195700%2FDM2-300x284.png%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685580%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22426%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFirst%2C%20according%20to%20Rodrik%E2%80%99s%20analytical%20framework%20above%2C%20and%20most%20directly%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3Eeconomic%20dislocation%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0can%20determine%20voters%E2%80%99%20preferences%20for%20policies%20and%20leaders%20(arrow%C2%A0%3Cem%3Ea%3C%2Fem%3E).%20Voters%20in%20a%20region%20where%20employment%20prospects%20have%20been%20adversely%20affected%20by%20a%20rise%20in%20imports%20may%20choose%20to%20cast%20their%20vote%20for%20a%20politician%20who%20advocates%20protectionism%20and%20a%20tougher%20line%20against%20foreign%20exporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESecond%2C%20economic%20dislocation%20may%20shape%20voters%E2%80%99%20preferences%20indirectly%20through%20the%20effect%20it%20has%20on%20identity%20or%20the%20salience%20of%20certain%20cultural%20values%20(arrow%C2%A0%3Cem%3Eb%3C%2Fem%3E).%20Concretely%2C%20economic%20shocks%20can%20heighten%20feelings%20of%20insecurity%2C%20inducing%20voters%20to%20make%20sharper%20distinctions%20between%20insiders%20(%E2%80%9Cus%E2%80%9D)%20and%20ethnic%2C%20religious%2C%20or%20racial%20outsiders%20(%E2%80%9Cthem%E2%80%9D).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThey%20can%20lead%20voters%20to%20yearn%20for%20an%20earlier%20era%20of%20prosperity%20and%20stability%2C%20increasing%20the%20political%20salience%20of%20traditional%20cultural%20values%20and%20hierarchies.%20And%20to%20the%20extent%20that%20they%20generate%20wider%20economic%20and%20social%20gaps%20within%20a%20nation%2C%20economic%20shocks%20may%20reinforce%20more%20local%2C%20less%20encompassing%20identities.%20To%20the%20extent%20that%20such%20effects%20operate%2C%20political%20preferences%20that%20appear%20to%20be%20driven%20by%20cultural%20values%20do%20in%20fact%20have%20deeper%20economic%20roots.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.routledge.com%2FStrongmen-Saviours-A-Political-Economy-of-Populism-in-India-Turkey-Russia%2FMohan-Padmanabhan%2Fp%2Fbook%2F9781032288314%5C%22%3Eexplored%20some%20of%20these%20links%3C%2Fa%3E%20between%20the%20discontents%20of%20neoliberal%20economics%20and%20populism%20in%20the%20context%20of%20India%2C%20Turkey%2C%20Brazil%20and%20Russia%3B%20however%2C%20there%20were%20other%20factors%20complementing%20this%20%E2%80%93%20and%20to%20Rodrik%E2%80%99s%20framework%20shared%20above.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwo%20additional%20causal%20factors%3A%20instances%20of%20large-scale%20public%20corruption%20(or%20an%20environment%20of%20perceived%20corrupt%20political%20elite)%2C%20and%20a%20rise%20in%20religious%20conservatism%20contributed%20to%20the%20rise%20of%20right-wing%20populist%20movements%20that%20subsequently%20brought%20leaders%20like%20Modi%2C%20Bolsonaro%20and%20Putin%20to%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-political-ethics-of-the-indian-political-right%5C%22%3Eis%20a%20critical%20need%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20put%20these%20explanations%20in%20both%20perspective%20and%20context%20while%20building%20upon%20what%20Gudavarthy%E2%80%99s%20and%20Oleksandr%E2%80%99s%20frame%20of%20reasoning%20brings%20in%20light%20by%20adopting%20a%20more%20neo-subaltern%20approach%20that%20is%20grounded%20in%20interpreting%20a%20random%20person%E2%80%99s%20influence%2Fpreference%20for%20the%20political%20right%20and%2For%20in%20explaining%20how%20the%20Right%20operates%20in%20influencing%20one%E2%80%99s%20everyday%20ethics%20%E2%80%93%20more%20distinctively%20and%20assertively%20%E2%80%93%20while%20thriving%20on%20the%20anxieties%2C%20fears%20and%20insecurities%20of%20the%20emotive%20majority%2C%20including%20those%20fuelled%20by%20negative%20emotions%20finding%20an%20agency%20of%20their%20own%20by%20Modi-Shah%E2%80%99s%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20lot%20more%20needs%20to%20be%20done%20in%20also%20understanding%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-political-ethics-of-the-indian-political-right%5C%22%3Ehow%20the%20moral-ethical%20core%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20an%20average%20Indian%20(a%20Hindu%20voter%20subscribing%20to%20the%20populist%20belief)%20remains%20influenced%20by%20the%20applied%20role%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fthe-political-ethics-of-the-indian-political-right%5C%22%3EDharam%2C%20Dharma%2C%20Kama%20and%20Karma%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20everyday%20life.%20A%20neo-subaltern%20ethnographic%20methodology%20may%20help%20explicate%20some%20of%20these%20new%20dimensions%20warranting%20a%20mixed-methods%20approach.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fmodi-adani-oligarchy-stock-offshore%5C%22%3Ethe%20conceptualisation%20of%20the%20new%20capital-state%E2%80%99s%20oligarghic%20rise%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20least%20in%20India%2C%20is%20linked%20to%20the%20nature%20of%20change%20seen%20in%20the%20global%20technological%20application%20of%20information%20technology%2C%20rise%20of%20new%20media%20(via%20social%20media)%20that%20weaponised%20a%20counter-narrative%20for%20extreme%20forms%20of%20radicalism%20amongst%20the%20masses%2C%20interplaying%20with%20their%20discontented%20feelings%20about%20neoliberal%20economic%20policies%20(leaving%20many%20of%20them%20worse%20off)%2C%20the%20breakdown%20of%20the%20old%20welfare%20state%20(creating%20an%20erosion%20of%20access%20to%20basic%20amenities)%2C%20rising%20corruption%2C%20and%20a%20moralistic-vacuum%20created%20in%20a%20%E2%80%98material-acquisitioning%E2%80%99%20capitalistic%20landscape%20(triggering%20a%20rise%20of%20conservatism%2C%20orthodoxy%2C%20and%20desiring%20a%20new%20moral-ethical%20code%20for%20everyday%20politics%2Faction%20of%20%3Cem%3Ebeing%3C%2Fem%3E%20under%20an%20authoritarian-neonationalist%20regime).%20We%20need%20a%20more%20case-dependent%2Fsensitive%20analysis%20of%20bringing%20an%20interpretative%20thread%20to%20these%20complex%20factors%2C%20explaining%20not%20just%20the%20rise%20but%20sustenance%20of%20neonationalism%20across%20the%20globe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDeepanshu%20Mohan%20is%20associate%20professor%20of%20economics%20and%20director%2C%20Centre%20for%20New%20Economics%20Studies%2C%20Jindal%20School%20of%20Liberal%20Arts%20and%20Humanities%2C%20O.P.%20Jindal%20Global%20University.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700530238000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F09%2F12140727%2FIMG_3148.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitical-economy%2Fwhat-explains-the-political-rights-ascendancy-to-global-power%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Instances%20of%20large-scale%20public%20corruption%20(or%20an%20environment%20of%20perceived%20corrupt%20political%20elite)%20and%20a%20rise%20in%20religious%20conservatism%2C%20in%20addition%20to%20other%20factors%2C%20contributed%20to%20the%20rise%20of%20right-wing%20populist%20movements.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%