ter%20of%20missile%20attacks%20on%20Ukraine%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221828%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Russian%20Vladimir%20Putin%20and%20Iran%20Ebrahim%20Raisi%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64bad14803c40c001a983a97%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22914%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ERussian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin%20and%20Iranian%20President%20Ebrahim%20Raisi%20in%20Samarkand%20in%20September%202022.%3Cp%3EALEXANDR%20DEMYANCHUK%2FSPUTNIK%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EA%20UN%20Security%20Council%20resolution%20passed%20in%20the%20days%20after%20the%202015%20Iran%20nuclear%20deal%20has%20expired.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThat%20could%20lead%20Russia%20to%20seek%20ballistic%20missiles%20from%20Iran%20as%20it%20steps%20up%20its%20attacks%20on%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIran%20has%20yet%20to%20provide%20those%20missiles%20to%20Russia%2C%20but%20their%20defense%20relationship%20has%20been%20expanding.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EThe%20day%20before%20UN%20restrictions%20on%20Iran's%20import%20and%20export%20of%20ballistic%20missiles%20and%20armed%20drones%20expired%20on%20October%2018%2C%20Russia%20declared%20it%20was%20no%20longer%20legally%20obligated%20to%20adhere%20to%20such%20restrictions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EThe%20declaration%20suggests%20Moscow%20may%20seek%20to%20refill%20its%20stocks%20with%20Iranian-made%20ballistic%20missiles.%20That%20could%20have%20ramifications%20for%20Ukraine%2C%20which%20is%20preparing%20for%20another%20winter%20of%20Russian%20missile%20and%20drone%20attacks%20on%20civilian%20and%20military%20infrastructure.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EUN%20Security%20Council%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.un.org%2Fsecuritycouncil%2Fcontent%2F2231%2Fbackground%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EResolution%202231%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20passed%20in%20July%202015%2C%20days%20after%20the%20US%20and%20Iran%20agreed%20on%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F2009-2017.state.gov%2Fe%2Feb%2Ftfs%2Fspi%2Firan%2Fjcpoa%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DOn%2520July%252014%252C%25202015%252C%2520the%2Cprogram%2520will%2520be%2520exclusively%2520peaceful.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Iran%20nuclear%20deal%3C%2Fa%3E.%20(The%20EU%2C%20the%20UK%2C%20France%2C%20Germany%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20China%20also%20signed%20the%20deal.)%20The%20resolution%20prohibited%20Tehran%20from%20exporting%20and%20importing%20missiles%20and%20drones%20with%20ranges%20exceeding%20186%20miles%20and%20payloads%20over%201%2C100%20pounds%20%E2%80%94%20limits%20suggested%20by%20the%20Missile%20Technology%20Control%20Regime%20%E2%80%94%20until%20October%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EThe%20US%20and%20the%20European%20signatories%20of%20the%20nuclear%20deal%20have%20decided%20to%20uphold%20sanctions%20against%20Iran's%20missile%20program%2C%20primarily%20because%20Tehran%20violated%20some%20terms%20of%20the%20agreement%20after%20Washington%20withdrew%20in%202018.%20They%20were%20also%20angered%20by%20Iran's%20decision%20to%20arm%20Russia%20with%20Shahed-131%20and%20-136%20one-way%20attack%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Iran%20Shahed-136%20Shahed-131%20drones%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655b96e922cf74a5739a30cf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221386%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EShahed-136%2C%20left%2C%20and%20Shahed-131%20drones%20on%20display%20at%20an%20IRGC%20facility%20in%20Tehran%20in%20October.%3Cp%3EMorteza%20Nikoubazl%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EThere%20has%20been%20persistent%20speculation%20about%20Iran%20supplying%20Russia%20with%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.axios.com%2F2022%2F12%2F12%2Fukraine-war-russia-missiles-iran-limit%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eshort-range%20ballistic%20missiles%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20or%20SRBMs%2C%20but%20that%20would%20almost%20certainly%20draw%20snapback%20sanctions%20under%20the%20resolution%20and%20Tehran%20has%20not%20yet%20done%20so.%20(While%20the%20ballistic-missile%20ban%20has%20expired%2C%20previous%20multilateral%20sanctions%20could%20be%20reimposed%20under%20a%20sunset%20clause%20option%20outlined%20under%202231%2C%20which%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aljazeera.com%2Fnews%2F2023%2F10%2F19%2Fhow-significant-is-lifting-of-un-curbs-on-irans-missile-programme%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eremains%20in%20effect%20until%202025%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3ENevertheless%2C%20the%20Russian%20Foreign%20Ministry's%20statement%20on%20October%2017%20suggests%20Moscow%20may%20seek%20Iranian%20short-range%20ballistic%20missiles%20to%20bolster%20its%20arsenal%20for%20another%20winter%20of%20attacks%20on%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BSupplies%20to%20and%20from%20Iran%20of%20products%20falling%20under%20the%20Missile%20Technology%20Control%20Regime%20no%20longer%20require%20prior%20approval%20by%20the%20UN%20Security%20Council%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fworld%2Frussia-says-it-need-no-longer-obey-un-restriction-missile-technology-iran-2023-10-17%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estatement%3C%2Fa%3E%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3ERussia%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frussia-searching-for-missiles-to-attack-ukraine-wont-run-out-2023-7%5C%22%3Econtinues%20to%20produce%20its%20own%20missiles%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20drones%2C%20but%20its%20constant%20attacks%20on%20Ukraine%20have%20strained%20its%20supplies.%20Last%20winter%2C%20when%20Moscow%20began%20using%20Iran's%20drones%2C%20it%20launched%201%2C000%20of%20them%20over%20six%20months%2C%20and%20Russian%20forces%20launched%20an%20estimated%20500%20drones%20against%20Ukrainian%20targets%20in%20September%20alone%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thedrive.com%2Fthe-war-zone%2Fukraine-situation-report-kyiv-prepares-for-unprecedented-winter-drone-war%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20new%20record%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EIf%20Moscow%20gets%20Iranian%20SRBMs%20now%2C%20Ukraine%20could%20face%20unprecedented%20pressure%2C%20but%20there%20are%20still%20doubts%20those%20missiles%20will%20end%20up%20in%20Russian%20hands.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Iran%20Zolfaghar%20Basir%20Dezful%20ballistic%20missiles%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655b96e922cf74a5739a30d1%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221364%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIran's%20Zolfaghar%20Basir%2C%20top%2C%20and%20Dezful%20short-%20and%20medium-range%20ballistic%20missiles%20in%20Tehran%20in%20January%202022.%3Cp%3EMorteza%20Nikoubazl%2FNurPhoto%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BFrankly%2C%20I%20don't%20think%20that%20the%20lifting%20of%20final%20sanctions%20under%20the%20UN%20resolution%20will%20greatly%20affect%20the%20possibility%20of%20Iranian%20ballistic%20missiles%20being%20supplied%20to%20Russia%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Anton%20Mardasov%2C%20a%20non-resident%20scholar%20with%20the%20Middle%20East%20Institute's%20Syria%20program.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EWhile%20Moscow%20requires%20%26quot%3Bas%20many%20high-precision%20weapons%26quot%3B%20as%20possible%2C%20it%20also%20%26quot%3Bdoesn't%20want%20to%20become%20completely%20dependent%26quot%3B%20on%20Tehran%2C%20Mardasov%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20The%20Russians%20are%20also%20hesitant%20to%20antagonize%20Israel%20or%20Arab%20Gulf%20countries%20by%20forging%20a%20strategic%20military%20alliance%20with%20their%20main%20regional%20rival.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3E%26quot%3BUnexpected%20decisions%20are%20possible%2C%20but%20for%20now%2C%20I%20am%20skeptical%20about%20the%20possibility%20of%20Iran%20supplying%20the%20Zolfaghar%20SRBM%20and%20other%20missiles%20to%20Russia%2C%26quot%3B%20Mardasov%20said%2C%20naming%20an%20Iranian%20missile%20with%20a%20range%20of%20just%20over%20400%20miles.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EResolution%202231's%20ban%20on%20Iran%20importing%20or%20exporting%20arms%20expired%20in%20October%202020.%20Since%20then%2C%20especially%20after%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20began%20in%20February%202022%2C%20there%20have%20been%20indications%20that%20Iran%20expected%20to%20receive%20two%20dozen%20Su-35%20fighter%20jets%20from%20Russia.%20Iran%20may%20also%20hope%20that%20in%20return%20for%20exporting%20drones%20to%20Russia%20and%20helping%20build%20them%20there%2C%20Moscow%20will%20license%20the%20production%20of%20other%20Russian%20military%20hardware%20in%20Iran.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EDespite%20%26quot%3Bpolitical%20games%26quot%3B%20involved%20in%20the%20Su-35%20contract%2C%20Mardasov%20expected%20it%20to%20be%20implemented%20%26quot%3Bin%20the%20medium-%20or%20even%20long-term%26quot%3B%20but%20said%20Moscow%20was%20less%20likely%20to%20export%20armored%20vehicles%20or%20helicopters%20to%20Iran%20due%20to%20demand%20on%20its%20defense%20industry%20to%20replenish%20Russian%20military%20stocks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221400%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Iran%20F-4%20fighter%20jet%20underground%20base%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F63e411ed96242f0019e80c09%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22934%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EIranian%20officials%20at%20an%20underground%20air%20base%20in%20February.%3Cp%3EIranian%20Army%2FHandout%2FAnadolu%20Agency%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3ERussia%20acknowledged%20in%20October%20that%20the%20war%20is%20straining%20its%20arms%20industry%2C%20with%20its%20own%20military's%20needs%20being%20prioritized.%20Accordingly%2C%20Moscow%20has%20proposed%20a%20new%20format%20for%20arms%20exports%2C%20including%20more%20substantial%20technology%20transfers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EThe%20head%20of%20Russian%20state%20arms%20firm%20Rosoboronexport%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Froe.ru%2Feng%2Fpress-service%2Fpress-releases%2Frosoboronexport-goes-on-to-work-on-technology-partnership-contracts-with-friendly-countries%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20October%2019%20that%20technology%20partnership%20contracts%20with%20foreign%20countries%20will%20offer%20%26quot%3Bopportunities%20to%20launch%20full-scale%20production%20on%20their%20territory%20and%20develop%20their%20own%20industrial%20base.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3ERosoboronexport%20has%20long%20licensed%20Indian%20production%20of%20a%20tailor-made%20version%20of%20the%20Su-30%20fighter%2C%20the%20Su-30MKI.%20There%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthediplomat.com%2F2016%2F02%2Fconfirmed-iran-and-russia-to-co-produce-su-30-fighter-jet%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereports%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20Iranian%20interest%20in%20manufacturing%20Su-30s%20under%20license.%20Tehran%20may%20also%20want%20to%20build%20later-model%20T-72%20and%20T-90%20tanks%20under%20license.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%3EFarzin%20Nadimi%2C%20a%20defense%20and%20security%20analyst%20at%20the%20Washington%20Institute%20for%20Near%20East%20Policy%2C%20said%20%26quot%3Ba%20series%20of%20technological%20exchanges%26quot%3B%20with%20Russia%20is%20Tehran's%20%26quot%3Bpreferred%20method%26quot%3B%20but%20one%20which%20Moscow%20hasn't%20previously%20offered.%3C