ations%20released%20from%20Russia's%20Ministry%20of%20Defense%20detail%20that%20exact%20strategy%20to%20their%20troops%2C%20indicating%20how%20each%20vehicle%20should%20be%20covered%20with%20cages%20to%20protect%20from%20unmanned%20aerial%20vehicles%20(UAVs).%20Although%20both%20sides%20of%20the%20war%20have%20previously%20used%20crude%20cages%20to%20contend%20with%20drones%2C%20Russia%20is%20apparently%20resigning%20itself%20to%20these%20limited%20defenses%20for%20the%20foreseeable%20future%20in%20a%20sign%20of%20how%20dominant%20and%20dangerous%20attack%20drones%20have%20become.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20Monday%2C%20illustrations%20from%20the%20ministry's%20main%20armored%20directorate%20were%20released%2C%20showing%20various%20methods%20for%20protecting%20equipment%20from%20first-person%20view%20(FPV)%20drones%20rigged%20with%20explosives%20and%20other%20UAV%20threats.%20In%20many%20cases%2C%20the%20ministry's%20official%20advice%20is%20to%20weld%20various%20shapes%20and%20sizes%20of%20cages%20to%20vehicles.%20Some%20illustrations%20show%20cages%20on%20top%20of%20tank%20turrets%2C%20while%20others%20show%20cages%20surrounding%20the%20sides%2C%20front%2C%20and%20back%20of%20vehicles.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22twitter%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20data-lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%20data-conversation%3D%5C%22undefined%5C%22%20data-cards%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%20%E2%80%94Samuel%20Bendett%20(%40sambendett)%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2Fmims%2Fstatuses%2F1726599531599720698%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3ENovember%2020%2C%202023%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20illustrations%20suggest%20how%20troops%20should%20array%20cages%20to%20maximize%20protection%20from%20exploding%20drones%2C%20such%20as%20constructing%20a%20barrier%20on%20top%20of%20a%20tank%20turret%20in%20such%20an%20angle%20that%20a%20drone%20can't%20find%20a%20way%20through%20the%20cage