credit%20card%20and%20bank%20account.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EMy%20parents%20taught%20me%20the%20value%20of%20money%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20grew%20up%20in%20a%20middle-class%20family%2C%20the%20third%20of%20four%20kids.%20I%20dressed%20in%20hand-me-downs%20or%20outfits%20my%20mom%20sewed%20herself%20or%20bought%20from%20discount%20bins.%20Instead%20of%20new%20Sasson%20jeans%20like%20the%20popular%20girls%20wore%2C%20I%20got%20my%20sister's%20old%20dungarees.%20I%20embroidered%20the%20back%20pockets%20and%20made%20them%20my%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20dad%20worked%20in%20advertising%20and%20my%20mom%20was%20a%20homemaker%20(Gen%20X%20for%20SAHM)%20and%20in%20charge%20of%20the%20household%20bills.%20When%20I%20was%20older%2C%20my%20mom%20got%20a%20part-time%20job%20and%20I%20remember%20how%20proud%20she%20was%20to%20earn%20her%20own%20money.%20Together%2C%20my%20parents%20saved%20enough%20to%20put%20four%20kids%20through%20college.%20To%20this%20day%2C%20I'm%20grateful%20for%20being%20unencumbered%20by%20student%20debt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cspan%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20manage%20our%20daily%20spending%20individually%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20husband%20and%20I%20married%20in%201990%20when%20I%20was%2023%20and%20he%20was%2026%20%E2%80%94%20young%20by%20today's%20standards%2C%20but%20common%20back%20then.%20We%20have%20never%20combined%20all%20our%20finances%20%E2%80%94%20and%20we%20have%20never%20shared%20a%20credit%20card%20%E2%80%94%20which%20has%20undoubtedly%20spared%20us%20countless%20arguments%20that%20might%20have%20seemed%20petty%20on%20the%20surface%20but%20could%20have%20inflicted%20deeper%20wounds.%20I%20buy%20what%20I%20want%2C%20when%20I%20want%2C%20and%20I%20can't%20imagine%20ever%20allowing%20my%20spending%20to%20be%20scrutinized%20%E2%80%94%20even%20by%20the%20person%20I%20trust%20the%20most.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20mom%20encouraged%20me%20to%20have%20my%20own%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fseparate-bank-account-fun-money-makes-budgeting-easier-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efun%20money%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%26quot%3B%20so%20I%20could%20indulge%20myself%20on%20occasion.%20Each%20month%2C%20my%20Visa%20statement%20includes%20small%20purchases%20I%20know%20my%20husband%20would%20deem%20unnecessary%20but%20that%20bring%20me%20comfort%20and%20pleasure.%20I%20will%20fiercely%20defend%20my%20right%20to%20impulse%20buy%20a%20pink-champagne%20cheek-lip-eye%20makeup%20stick%2C%20another%20musk-scented%20candle%2C%20or%20one%20more%20book%20despite%20my%20teetering%20stacks%20still%20waiting%20to%20be%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20have%20separate%20credit%20cards%2C%20bank%20accounts%2C%20and%20retirement%20funds%3B%20we%20share%20our%20investment%20funds%20and%20have%20a%20joint%20bank%20account%20for%20moving%20cash%20between%20us.%20For%20simplicity%2C%20I%20pay%20the%20household%20bills%20and%20he%20pays%20the%20insurance%20premiums%20out%20of%20our%20own%20accounts%2C%20and%20if%20one%20of%20us%20runs%20short%2C%20the%20other%20transfers%20money%20to%20our%20joint%20account.%20We%20consider%20our%20expenses%20equally%20shared%20%E2%80%94%20no%20need%20for%20bean%20counting%20or%20reimbursing%20one%20another.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHaving%20my%20own%20accounts%20gives%20me%20freedom%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20don't%20consult%20my%20husband%20on%20day-to-day%20purchases%2C%20but%20I%20don't%20hide%20them%20either.%20I'm%20transparent%20regarding%20my%20assets%2C%20and%20my%20husband%20is%2C%20too.%20We%20both%20enjoy%20the%20freedom%20to%20spend%20within%20reason%20because%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fspending-vs-saving-my-partner-and-dont-always-agree-2023-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eour%20financial%20strategies%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20aligned.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPerhaps%20getting%20married%20so%20young%20helped.%20Not%20only%20were%20our%20views%20shaped%20by%20the%20same%20influences%2C%20they%20were%20also%20shaped%20together.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20early%20on%2C%20we%20took%20a%20conservative%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fspouse-partner-helping-teach-me-about-budgeting-2023-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eapproach%20to%20money%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20partially%20by%20following%20my%20parents'%20example.%20We%20charge%20only%20what%20we%20can%20pay%20in%20full%2C%20make%20all%20major%20purchase%20decisions%20together%2C%20and%20squirrel%20away%20a%20little%20each%20month%20for%20our%20investment%20funds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20our%20daughter%20was%20born%2C%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20opened%20a%20529%20savings%20plan%20for%20college.%20Shortly%20after%2C%20each%20of%20us%20became%20self-employed%2C%20which%20meant%20it%20fell%20on%20us%20to%20contribute%20to%20our%20IRAs%20and%20buy%20health%20insurance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20habits%20we%20established%20served%20us%20well%20when%20our%20daughter%20was%20diagnosed%20with%20cystic%20fibrosis%2C%20a%20life-threatening%20chronic%20illness.%20Our%20financial%20priorities%20were%20clear%3A%20Pay%20for%20the%20best%20health%20coverage%20available%2C%20and%20save%20for%20the%20future%20in%20case%20she%20ever%20needs%20help%20with%20medical%20or%20living%20expenses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEach%20year%2C%20we%20faced%20the%20sticker%20shock%20of%20rising%20health%20insurance%20costs%2C%20and%20I%20made%20the%20same%20comment%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20never%20want%20to%20look%20back%20and%20regret%20not%20getting%20her%20the%20treatment%20she%20needed.%26quot%3B%20My%20husband%20agreed.%20Of%20all%20the%20things%20we've%20accomplished%20as%20a%20couple%2C%20putting%20her%20first%20is%20what%20I'm%20most%20proud%20of.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20my%20dad%20died%2C%20my%20mom%20knew%20where%20their%20money%20was%20and%20how%20to%20manage%20it%2C%20which%20isn't%20always%20the%20case%20with%20women%20of%20her%20generation.%20While%20my%20dad%20taught%20me%20about%20mutual%20funds%2C%20dollar%20cost%20averaging%2C%20and%20how%20to%20sa