3%2F11%2F02135655%2FF9XZ5mwbwAATvWn.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20central%20project%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20military%20reforms%20%E2%80%93%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Findia-military-operational-commands-theatres-map-proposal%5C%22%3EIntegrated%20Theatre%20Commands%3C%2Fa%3E%20(ITCs)%20for%20jointness%20in%20combat%20%E2%80%93%20has%20once%20again%20fallen%20through%20the%20cleavage%20of%20over-ambition%20and%20half-baked%20ideas.%20This%20is%20a%20substantial%20setback%20for%20the%20office%20of%20the%20Chief%20of%20Defense%20Staff%20(CDS)%2C%20whose%20primary%20job%20was%20to%20create%20ITCs%20after%20directing%20the%20three%20service%20chiefs%20to%20find%20consensus%20among%20themselves.%20This%20is%20not%20because%20India%20needs%20the%20ITCs%2C%20but%20because%20to%20retain%20the%20retiring%2C%20but%20ideologically%20aligned%20army%20chief%20General%20Bipin%20Rawat%20in%20uniform%2C%20the%20government%20on%20December%2030%2C%202019%20created%20the%20office%20of%20the%20CDS%2C%20under%20the%20ruse%20of%20military%20reforms.%20Within%20days%2C%20Rawat%20announced%20that%20implementation%20of%20the%20ITCs%20after%20acceptance%20by%20the%20three%20services%20(army%2C%20air%20force%2C%20navy)%20will%20commence%20in%20December%202022%2C%20at%20the%20end%20of%20his%20three-year%20term.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEven%20after%20four%20years%2C%20the%20military%20reforms%20remain%20on%20the%20drawing%20board%2C%20there%20are%20clearly%20problems%20with%20them%20that%20Rawat%2C%20and%20after%20his%20untimely%20death%2C%20his%20successor%2C%20General%20Anil%20Chauhan%20were%20trying%20to%20thrust%20upon%20the%20Indian%20military.%20The%20biggest%20is%20that%20they%20are%20outdated%2C%20being%2022%20years%20old.%20Following%20the%201999%20Kargil%20conflict%20with%20Pakistan%2C%20the%20Group%20of%20Ministers%20(GoM)%20had%2C%20in%20February%202001%2C%20recommended%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20CDS%20post%20to%20usher%20in%20jointness%20amongst%20the%20services.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESince%20then%2C%20China%2C%20instead%20of%20Pakistan%2C%20has%20emerged%20as%20India%E2%80%99s%20primary%20military%20threat%20with%20capabilities%20to%20fight%20in%20six%20physical%20and%20virtual%20war%20domains%20of%20land%2C%20air%2C%20sea%2C%20outer%20space%2C%20cyberspace%2C%20and%20electromagnetic%20spectrum%20space%2C%20and%20capacities%20(indigenous%20defence%20industrial%20complex)%20to%20support%20these%20domains%20with%20war%20surge%20without%20outside%20support.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENow%2C%20military%20reforms%20are%20done%20for%20two%20reasons%3A%20One%2C%20to%20improve%20war%20concepts%20(how%20to%20fight)%20to%20optimise%20war%20domains%E2%80%99%20usage%20to%20exercise%20control%20over%20war%20aims%2C%20speed%2C%20tempo%2C%20intensity%2C%20and%20outcome.%20And%20two%2C%20to%20use%20military%20power%20beyond%20guarding%20one%E2%80%99s%20territorial%20sovereignty%20to%20influence%20global%20events%20(called%20out-of-area%20operations).%20By%202013%2C%20China%20had%20met%20both%20conditions%20for%20military%20reforms.%20By%202010%2C%20the%20People%E2%80%99s%20Liberation%20Army%20(PLA)%20had%20developed%20its%20six%20war%20domains%2C%20and%20in%202013%2C%20Chinese%20President%20Xi%20Jinping%20announced%20his%20ambitious%20Belt%20and%20Road%20Initiative%20(BRI)%20which%20required%20the%20PLA%20to%20protect%20Chinese%20infrastructure%2C%20assets%2C%20and%20people%20in%20nations%20onboard%20the%20BRI.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EGiven%20this%2C%20China%20announced%20its%20expansive%202015%20military%20reforms%20to%20be%20completed%20in%20five%20years%20and%20under%20which%20it%20created%20Western%20Theatre%20Command%20(WTC)%20for%20joint%20combat%20with%20the%20Indian%20military%20on%20the%20disputed%20border.%20Interestingly%2C%20a%20reforms%20committee%20formed%20under%20China%E2%80%99s%20Central%20Military%20Commission%20(the%20highest%20military%20policy-making%20body%20headed%20by%20Xi%20Jinping)%20in%202012%20took%20three%20years%20to%20work%20on%20reforms%20at%20the%20grandest%20and%20most%20granular%20levels%20before%20declaring%20them%20to%20the%20world.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESadly%2C%20the%20Indian%20military%20missed%20the%20PLA%E2%80%99s%20upward%20trajectory%20since%20it%20kept%20its%20sights%20low%20doing%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fpoliticising-the-armed-forces-has-consequences%5C%22%3Ecounter-terror%20operations%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Jammu%20and%20Kashmir%20since%201991%20and%2C%20on%20contemplating%20building%20deterrence%20(military%20power)%20against%20the%20Pakistan%20military.%20Hence%2C%20the%20US%20Pentagon%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapps.dtic.mil%2Fsti%2Fpdfs%2FAD1126529.pdf%5C%22%3Ethird%20offset%20strategy%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20negate%20the%20PLA%E2%80%99s%20conventional%20war%20advantage%20through%20the%20infusion%20of%20artificial%20intelligence%20and%20autonomy%20declared%20in%202014%20went%20unnoticed%20by%20the%20Indian%20military%20leadership.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%2C%20when%20Rawat%20started%20work%20on%20ITCs%2C%20he%2C%20without%20constituting%20a%20reforms%20committee%2C%20made%20his%20own%20assumptions%20on%20the%20wars%20that%20India%20should%20prepare%20for%20with%20Pakistan%20and%20China.%20He%20shared%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eperiodic%20and%20piecemeal%20revelations%20of%20his%20vision%20for%20a%20year%20and%20a%20half%20with%20select%20media%2C%20and%20finally%20unveiled%20his%20military%20reform%20plan%20in%20a%20television%20interview%20on%20July%202%2C%202021.%20According%20to%20him%2C%20since%20future%20wars%20would%20be%20at%20short%20notice%20and%20of%20short%20duration%2C%20it%20was%20necessary%20that%20all%20war%20domains%20(army%2C%20air%20force%2C%20and%20navy)%20should%20have%20jointness%20(where%20domains%20fight%20together%20and%20as%20one%20whole)%20and%20integration%20for%20synergy%20(where%20each%20domain%20has%20cross-domain%20capability%2C%20making%20the%20total%20more%20effective%20than%20the%20whole).%20Moreover%2C%20in%20ITCs%2C%20since%20a%20theatre%20commander%20should%20have%20assets%20permanently%20under%20his%20command%2C%20he%20would%20be%20able%20to%20assemble%20a%20%E2%80%98joint%20force%E2%80%99%20quickly%20to%20achieve%20a%20given%20mission.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERawat%E2%80%99s%20plan%20had%20four%20big%20operational%20flaws.%20One%2C%20since%20the%20PLA%20can%20fight%20in%20six%20war%20domains%20against%20three%20of%20the%20Indian%20military%2C%20it%20will%20combat%20at%20strategic%20(cyber%2C%20space%2C%20information%20war)%20or%20whole-of-nation%20level%2C%20and%20operational%20or%20campaign%20level%20totally%20bypassing%20the%20tactical%20level%20or%20battles%20where%20attrition%20happens.%20Recall%2C%20the%201991%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fhistory.army.mil%2Fhtml%2Fbookshelves%2Fresmat%2Fdesert-storm%2Findex.html%5C%22%3EOperation%20Desert%20Storm%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20the%20US%20military%20conducted%20a%2043-day%20intense%20air%20campaign%20against%20the%20Iraqi%20army%2C%20followed%20by%20100%20hours%20of%20mopping%20up%20operations%20on%20the%20ground.%20However%2C%20war%20with%20Pakistan%20will%20be%20different%20since%20both%20Indian%20and%20Pakistan%20militaries%20fight%20attrition%20wars%20at%20tactical%20levels.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ETwo%2C%20whether%20a%20war%20between%20India%20and%20China%20will%20be%20short%20or%20long%20would%20be%20determined%20by%20the%20stronger%20side.%20So%2C%20China%20will%20decide%20this%20depending%20upon%20the%20war%20objectives%20it%20wishes%20to%20accomplish.%20Three%2C%20unlike%20China%2C%20India%20does%20not%20have%20a%20vibrant%20defence%20industrial%20complex%20to%20support%20even%20an%20intense%20short%20war%20against%20the%20PLA.%20And%20four%2C%20it%20is%20not%20possible%20for%20India%20to%20fight%20three%20different%20wars%20with%20China%2C%20Pakistan%2C%20and%20counter-terror%20operations%20in%20Kashmir%20simultaneously.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStrangely%2C%20the%20above%20operational%20flaws%20do%20not%20seem%20to%20bother%20the%20military%20leadership.%20Their%20concerns%20are%20three-fold.%20First%2C%20how%20to%20accommodate%20senior%20officers%20of%20the%20present%20seventeen%20separate%20military%20commands%20of%20the%20three%20services%20into%20three%20or%20four%20ITCs.%20Hence%2C%20talks%20are%20going%20on%20to%20create%20more%20integrated%20commands%20for%20logistics%2C%20missiles%20and%20so%20on.%20Second%2C%20the%20Indian%20Air%20Force%20(rightly%20so)%20is%20unwilling%20to%20permanently%20part%20with%20its%20limited%20combat%20aircraft%20to%20the%20ITCs.%20And%20three%2C%20services%20chiefs%20who%20are%20both%20topmost%20staff%20officers%20(force%20providers)%20and%20operational%20commanders%20(force%20employers)%20of%20their%20respective%20services%20are%20not%20agreeable%20to%20giving%20up%20their%20force%20employers%20role%20to%20ITC%20commanders.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20need%20is%20to%20abandon%20ITCs%20and%20focus%20on%20building%20the%20science%20of%20war%20(technologies)%20and%20the%20art%20of%20war%20(war%20concepts)%20concurrently.%20And%20hope%20that%20there%20is%20no%20war%20with%20China%20or%20Pakistan%20since%20both%20are%20joined%20at%20the%20hip.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fpravin-sawhney%5C%22%3EPravin%20Sawhney%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20the%20author%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Last%20War%3A%20How%20AI%20Will%20Shape%20India%E2%80%99s%20Final%20Showdown%20With%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700479763000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F02135655%2FF9XZ5mwbwAATvWn.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fover-ambition-half-baked-ideas-military-integrated-theatre-commands%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22There%20are%20at%20least%20four%20operational%20flaws%20with%20the%20ITC%20overhaul.%20But%20they%20do%20not%20seem%20to%20bother%20the%20military%20leadership.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fover-ambition-half-baked-ideas-military-integrated-theatre-commands%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Recovery%20rate%20from%20personal%20guarantors%20to%20rise%20after%20SC%20decision%3A%20CareEdge%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1700478290000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fbsmedia.business-standard.com%2F_media%2Fbs%2Fimg%2Farticle%2F2021-09%2F29%2Ffull%2F1632854134-9064.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Frecovery-rate-from-personal-guarantors-to-rise-after-sc-decision-careedge-123112000649_1.html%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Supreme%20Court%20upheld%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20IBC%20provisions%20on%20Personal%20Guarantors'%20Insolvency%20Resolution%2C%20dismissing%20over%20200%20petitions%20which%20challenged%20its%20legal%20validity%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Frecovery-rate-from-personal-guarantors-to-rise-after-sc-decision-careedge-123112000649_1.html%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-business--standard-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Frecovery-rate-from-personal-guarantors-to-rise-after-sc-decision-careedge-123112000649_1.html%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.business-standard.com%2Famp%2Fcompanies%2Fnews%2Frecovery-rate-from-personal-guarantors-to-rise-after-sc-decision-careedge-123112000649_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Shakira%3A%20Singer%20settles%20Spanish%20tax%20fra